Several police officers have spoken out against the recent spate of officers being killed. CAPE TOWN - Several police officers in the Western Cape have spoken out against the recent spate of officers being killed.Five officers have been murdered in separate incidents in Cape Town over the past three weeks.In the latest incident on Monday, a constable was gunned down outside his home in Kraaifontein.Police officers, who attended the provincial fitness policy and Back-To-Basics approach launch earlier on Wednesday, say enough is enough. We cannot allow criminals to go around shooting our colleagues. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)